                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "THCOL"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The thermal column of the Livermore reactor in",
                "a flux of 2.e11 n/(cm2 sec) (cadmium ratio 600).",
                "Data were accumulated alternately with the reactor on",
                "and then off. Two separate runs of about three weeks",
                "each were made."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COINC",
                "PHD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The fragment masses for each event were",
                "calculated from the kinetic energies, assuming",
                "conservation of momentum and mass."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Two Si detectors with collimators to limit the",
                "maximum fragment entry angle to 50 degrees from the",
                "normal to the detectors"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "MONITOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "233U source (2 ng) for neutron-flux determination and",
                "a check on the energy calibration,",
                "252Cf spontaneous-fission source for energy",
                "calibration"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The sample, containing 4.e8 atoms of 257Fm, was",
                "obtained from the Hutch underground nuclear explosion.",
                "After final purification, a few microliters of solution",
                "containing 257Fm was evaporated on a 200-micro-g/cm2 Pt",
                "foil."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "A correction was made for the pulse-height defect but",
                "not for neutron emission."
              ]
            }
          ],
